com.avaya.csta.binding

Class AvayaEvents

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.AvayaEvents
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AvayaEvents
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Specifies which types of events should be monitored. By default, all event types are monitored. If a specific event is NOT desired, then a filter for the event class should be included with the element for the undesired event set to true. Note that Avaya has also defined an invertFilter flag in this structure that allows an application to specify only those events that they are interested in receiving. If the invertFilter flag is set to true, then a filter should be included with a value of true for events that the application wishes to receive. The invertFilter flag applies to both standard and Avaya-specific events for the entire MonitorStart request.
